  "text": "Age-and sex-matched mice were sacrificed, bone marrow cells were recovered from tibiae and femora and erythrocytes were lysed. After 24 hours of incubation, non-adherent cells were collected and cultured on non-tissue culture dishes for selection in RPMI supplemented with 10% fetal calf serum (FCS), 50 IU/ml penicillin and 30% L929 conditioned medium as a source of CSF-1. Cells used in assays were grown for 7-10 days in culture and were transferred to tissue culture plates overnight before use (n5number of independent BMDM preparations per genotype). MEFs were grown in high-glucose DMEM (PAA) supplemented with 50 IU/ml penicillin, 50/ml streptomycin and 10% FCS (PAA). Generation of p14 f/-and p14 2/2 MEFs was described previously [CITATION_1] .",
